  "title": "Contracts Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Support and manage the tender process, from initial assessment to submission.</p>\n<p>· Prepare and review tender documents, ensuring compliance with industry standards and client requirements.</p>\n<p>· Liaise with internal departments to gather necessary information and ensure timely delivery of tender submissions.</p>\n<p>· Work closely with Commercial Contract personnel to ensure compliance on contractual obligations, agreements, and other legal documents related to maintenance and facilities management services.</p>\n<p>· Ensure all contracts comply with company policies, legal regulations, and industry standards.</p>\n<p>· Negotiate pricings and terms and conditions with clients and vendors to secure favourable agreements.</p>\n<p>· Ensure continual support on contractual change order management throughout contract period.</p>\n<p>· Serve as the point of contact for contract-related matters with clients and vendors.</p>\n<p>· Foster strong relationships with clients and vendors, addressing any concerns or issues that may arise.</p>\n<p>· Coordinate with clients and vendors to ensure seamless execution of maintenance and facilities management services.</p>\n<p>· Maintain accurate and up-to-date records of all contracts, agreements, and correspondence.</p>\n<p>· Prepare regular reports on contract status, performance metrics, and compliance issues for senior management.</p>\n<p>· Assist in the development and implementation of contract management policies and procedures.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Degree/Diploma with at least 1 year of experience in QS/engineering roles.</p>\n<p>(ITE holder with relevant years of experience or fresh degree/diploma holder can be considered).</p>\n<p>· Detail-oriented with strong analytical and problem-solving abilities.</p>\n<p>· Positive proactive attitude and ethical behaviour.</p>\n<p>· Team player with ability to work independently and resolve challenges in a fast-paced environment.</p>\n<p>· Excellent interpersonal, communication, collaborative and people management skills.</p>\n<p>· Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint).</p>",
